A Grease spell covers a material surface with a slippery, highly flamable layer of a fatty, greasy nature. Any creature entering the area or caught in it when the spell is cast must save vs. Spell at +2 or slip and slide, unable to move effectively (80% slower). Those who successfully save can move, albeit slowly (25% slower), for the rest of the round (but will need to save vs. Spell again the following round). Regardless of whether they save against the effect or not, the oil will make them take 25% more fire damage for 1 round due to the volatile nature of the oils. Those who remain in the area are allowed a saving throw each round until they escape the area.

